  "prompt": "How much cubic meter of cement, sand required for 12mm cement sand plaster 1:6 for 950 sq m?",
  "response": "To calculate the quantities of cement and sand required for a 12mm thick plaster for an area of 950 square meters with a mix ratio of 1:6 (cement:sand), we'll follow these steps:\n\n1. **Calculate the volume of plaster required**:\n   - Area = 950 sq m\n   - Thickness = 12 mm = 0.012 m\n   - Volume of plaster = Area \u00d7 Thickness = 950 m\u00b2 \u00d7 0.012 m = 11.4 m\u00b3\n\n2. **Calculate the total parts of the mix**:\n   - The ratio of cement to sand is 1:6, which means there are a total of \\(1 + 6 = 7\\) parts.\n\n3. **Calculate the quantities of cement and sand**:\n   - Volume of cement = (1/7) \u00d7 total volume of plaster\n   - Volume of sand = (6/7) \u00d7 total volume of plaster\n\n   Now calculate:\n   - Volume of cement = (1/7) \u00d7 11.4 m\u00b3 \u2248 1.63 m\u00b3\n   - Volume of sand = (6/7) \u00d7 11.4 m\u00b3 \u2248 9.77 m\u00b3\n\n### Summary of Requirements:\n- Cement required: \u2248 **1.63 cubic meters**\n- Sand required: \u2248 **9.77 cubic meters**\n\nMake sure to account for wastage and moisture content during construction, which can affect the exact quantities needed.",
